# Thinking Guides

## Scope

Shared project-wide workflow rules used by all packages and layers.

## Pre-Development Checklist

- Read `.superwork/workflow.md`
- Read the relevant package/layer `index.md`
- Choose `superwork-brainstorming` for design-heavy feature work
- Choose `superwork-tdd` for direct feature work, but save `.superwork/plans/*.md` before the first RED test
- Choose `superwork-debugging` for bug work
- Reserve `superwork-code-simplifier` for behavior-preserving cleanup after the change is already green

## Verification Checklist

- Run fresh verification before any completion claim
- follow `superwork-check` before final completion: if the diff is medium or large, must run `superwork-code-simplifier`; if it is skipped, state why the current diff is truly small and does not need behavior-preserving cleanup
- Use project-local commands such as:
{{ test_hints }}

## Update Triggers

- A new cross-package rule was introduced
- A repeated bug pattern needs durable guidance
- A verification requirement now applies across the project
